703697f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - Bush Street
703697f-a.text:
Clinton Street, north from Bush Street, showing (left) the fenced-off area on the west side of the street where the Red Hook Houses, a housing center sponsored by the New York
City Housing Authority, was erected.
P. L. Sperr  April 9, 1939
